<div1 type="letter">
<pb facs="nei.n1b.3.7"/>
<fw type="curatorial">7</fw>

<opener>
<address>
<addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505</addrLine> 
</address>
<dateline>April 9, 1971</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>Dr. Bower Aly</addrLine> 
<addrLine>Department of Speech</addrLine> 
<addrLine>University of Oregon</addrLine>
<addrLine>Eugene, Oregon 97403</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
</opener>

<p>Bless your heart and many thanks. I certainly do deeply appreciate what you have just done in the
interest of the Dick Cavett show and my work generally. Your latest efforts are too characteristic
for thanks and I feel almost guilty when I thank you again (nevertheless, please don't quit!). I
note that the Dick Cavett address that you give is not quite correct. It should be American
Broadcasting Company, 1790 Broadway, New York, N. Y. 10019.</p> 
<p>It does look as though there is a ground swell of interest in my stuff. It's a constant surprise to
me.</p> 
<p>I have just signed an option contract with a movie producer.</p> 
<p>I do want to know more about Lucile's progress with the revision job. It's going to be a great day
when we see that in print.</p>

<closer>
<salute>With the old affection,</salute>
<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

<note type="authorial">JGN:nh</note>

